# Supabase Configuration
# =====================================================
# IMPORTANT: Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual Supabase credentials
# Get these values from your Supabase project dashboard at https://app.supabase.com
# 
# Steps to set up:
# 1. Go to your Supabase project dashboard
# 2. Click on "Settings" in the left sidebar
# 3. Click on "API" under Project Settings
# 4. Copy the "Project URL" and paste it below as SUPABASE_URL
# 5. Copy the "anon public" key and paste it below as SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# 6. Save this file as .env (remove the .example extension)
# =====================================================

# Your Supabase project URL (e.g., https://xxxxxxxxxxxxx.supabase.co)
SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url_here

# Your Supabase anonymous/public key (starts with eyJ...)
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# =====================================================
# SECURITY NOTES:
# - Never commit the .env file to version control
# - The .env file should be added to .gitignore
# - The anon key is safe to use in client-side code
# - For admin operations, you'll need to set up Row Level Security (RLS)
# =====================================================